<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0" Background="#1E1F22" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="14" PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">Styles</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">How Style.TMA files define wall texture recipes used by the Map Editor when painting building facets.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">What Are Styles?</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Each texture world has a <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">Style.TMA</Run> file. This file defines the wall texture recipes used to paint building facets in the Map Editor.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>A style is not just one texture. It is a recipe made from several texture slots. The game and editor use these recipes to build the visible wall patterns on building facets.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_overview.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8"><Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0"><Run FontWeight="Bold">Note:</Run><Run> When you create a new custom world, a new Style.TMA file is automatically created and loaded into the TMA Styles section.</Run></TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">TMA Styles Section</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>The <Bold>TMA Styles</Bold> section lists the style entries available for the current texture world. There are up to <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">199</Run> editable style slots.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_tma_styles_section.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Loading an Existing Style.TMA</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>You can load a previously saved <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">Style.TMA</Run> file from another folder, but styles reference texture numbers from the world they were created for. A style file from another world may not line up correctly with your custom textures.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_load_existing_tma.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8"><Border Background="#3A2A2A" BorderBrush="#7A4A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0A0A0"><Run FontWeight="Bold">⚠ Important:</Run><Run> Loading a Style.TMA from another world can produce unexpected wall textures because the recipes may reference different texture cells.</Run></TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Editing a Style Entry</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Double-click a style number in the TMA Styles list, such as <Bold>Style #1</Bold>, to open the <Bold>Edit Style Window</Bold>.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_double_click_style_entry.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_edit_style_window.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9ECBFF">Style Name</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Enter a descriptive style name for easy reference, such as Brick Wall, Shop Front, Warehouse Concrete, or Glass Office Wall.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_style_name_field.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">The Five Recipe Slots</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Each style contains five texture recipe slots. These define the pieces the renderer can use when drawing a facet. The exact appearance depends on facet height, orientation, and wall settings.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_recipe_slots.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8"><Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF"><Run FontWeight="Bold">Tip:</Run><Run> In the current editor preview/model, Slot 3 is treated as the left-side piece of the wall recipe. To understand a recipe clearly, make each slot a different test colour and apply it to a simple wall.</Run></TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Choosing a Texture for a Slot</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Click a slot preview image to open the <Bold>Pick Texture</Bold> window. You can choose from World Textures or Shared Textures.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_click_slot_preview.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_pick_texture_window.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Slot Flags</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Each recipe slot has flags that affect how the selected texture is drawn in that slot.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_slot_flags.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Flip X</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Flips the selected slot texture horizontally.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Flip Y</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Flips the selected slot texture vertically.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Gour</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Enables Gouraud-style shading, a smooth vertex-based lighting technique where brightness or colour is interpolated across the surface.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Tex</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Marks the slot as using a texture. This is normally enabled for ordinary wall recipes.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Mask</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Enables mask-style rendering for the slot.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Trans</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Enables transparent or translucent drawing behaviour for the slot.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Tile</Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">Enables tiled or repeated drawing behaviour for the slot.</Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">How Styles Are Used by the Map Editor</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>In the Map Editor, building facets reference style data through their facet style information. A positive style value points to a TMA style number. Tall, two-sided, or two-textured walls may use additional style entries or bands.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_map_editor_wall_example.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Saving a Style</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>After changing the style name, selected textures, or slot flags, press <Bold>Save</Bold> in the Edit Style Window. This saves the updated entry back into the current <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">Style.TMA</Run> file.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/styles_save_style_entry.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
</FlowDocument>
